        <h2>Integration</h2>
        <p>The ALIVE layers are related one to another. These relations are established with mappings defined across their meta-elements. Predefined transformations that are part of the ALIVE toolset implement those mappings and generate the corresponding parts. </p>
<h3>Organisation - Coordination</h3>
        <p>The Organisation and Coordination models are related upon the following elements.</p>
        <center><table border="1" width="80%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr bgcolor="#eeece1">
            <td width="50%" valign="top"><strong>Organisation</strong></td>
            <td width="50%" valign="top"><strong>Coordination</strong></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Objective with no sub-objectives</td>
            <td valign="top">AtomicAction</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Objective with sub-objectives</td>
            <td valign="top">CompositeAction<br />
              subObjectives are constructed with an   anyorder construct</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Objective with a Negation as State   description </td>
            <td valign="top">ActionResult that hasDeleteEffect   Expression</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Objective with any other type as State   description</td>
            <td valign="top">ActionResult that hasAddEffect   Expression</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Landmarks of an interactionPattern</td>
            <td valign="top">CompositeAction<br />
              The entailed Objective are constructed   with an anyorder construct</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">LandmarkPattern of a scene</td>
            <td valign="top">CompositeAction<br />
              Ordered landmarks are constructed with   a sequence construct</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Scene</td>
            <td valign="top">CompositeAction<br />
              The interactionPatterns are constructed   with an anyorder construct</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">IS</td>
            <td valign="top">CompositeAction<br />
              Ordered scenes are constructed with a   sequence construct</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Player</td>
            <td valign="top">Participant</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Role</td>
            <td valign="top">Agent</td>
          </tr>
        </table></center>
        <p>The actual relationships are formalised with an Opera2Actions and Opera2Agents mapping descriptions. </p>
        <p> The Opera2Actions transformation does not provide a complete action model, but a framework that the developer has to elaborate further with additional details such as to combine actions together. Further an Actions2Task transformation would provide the corresponding task model. Finally, the Opera2Agents transformation will generate the agents that will be injected on the agentscape. </p>
<h3>Coordination - Services</h3>
        <p>The Coordination and Service models are related upon the following elements.</p>
        <center><table border="1"  width="60%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
          <tr bgcolor="#eeece1">
            <td width="50%" valign="top"><strong>Coordination</strong></td>
            <td width="50%" valign="top"><strong>Services</strong></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Plan</td>
            <td valign="top">Service</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Task of a plan</td>
            <td valign="top">Interface of a service</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Perform Action</td>
            <td valign="top">Operation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Action’s Inputs</td>
            <td valign="top">Message Input</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td valign="top">Action’s Outputs</td>
            <td valign="top">Message Output</td>
          </tr>
        </table></center>
        <p>These relationships are formalised with a CL2SL mapping description. In addition a number of configuration parameters need to be defined in order to provide fully generated service description.</p>
